# KiCad MCP Python Configuration Example

# Path to KiCad CLI executable
KICAD_CLI_PATH=/Applications/KiCad/KiCad.app/Contents/MacOS/kicad-cli

# === NEW PROJECT-BASED APPROACH (Recommended) ===
# Specify project directories - the system will auto-detect all KiCad projects
# Multiple directories can be specified, comma-separated
PROJECT_PATHS=/path/to/project1/,/path/to/project2/,/path/to/projects/directory/

# Example:
# PROJECT_PATHS=/Volumes/Vault/Workspace/kicad-development/mcp-test-project,/Users/username/KiCadProjects

# === LEGACY FILE-BASED APPROACH (Still Supported) ===
# Specify individual PCB files - used as fallback if PROJECT_PATHS not set
# PCB_PATHS=/path/to/project1.kicad_pcb,/path/to/project2.kicad_pcb

# Example:
# PCB_PATHS=/Volumes/Vault/Workspace/kicad-development/mcp-test-project/mcp-test-project.kicad_pcb

# === BENEFITS OF NEW APPROACH ===
# - Auto-detects all project files (.kicad_pro, .kicad_sch, .kicad_pcb, etc.)
# - Supports future schematic editor integration
# - Detects project status (active editing, backups, etc.)
# - Easier project management - just specify directories
# - Forward compatible with KiCad API extensions